==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palpitation
<hw>Pal`pi*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>palpitatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>palpitation</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
rapid pulsation; a throbbing; esp., an abnormal, rapid beating of the
heart as when excited by violent exertion, strong emotion, or by
disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

